		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=51502">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Hizuka" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Hizuka">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Hizuka" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=65&FN=Monk&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1300239&TN=Help+me+out+please&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1300250&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Well, for bags, I did fine with a small bag until I was near 40 and finally got a weight-reducing one in CC.  That kind of bag isn't cheap.</P><P>If you want reassurance, try this:  every time the question comes up on Monkly-Business, lots of people say STA, including some very well-known figures, and lots more say they wish they'd put it all in stamina.  Basically, if you nose around monk gear a bit, you'll find that STA is the rarest combat stat, while it seems nearly every piece has STR, DEX, and/or AGI.</P><P>The benefits are higher HP (a few hundred at 60), less fatigue drain, and most importantly, if you run out of endurance, you don't receive attack speed and stat penalties if your stamina is at least 100.</P><P>I would replace those jagged bands with, say 5/55 rings, or 6/65 if you can afford them.  For bracers, understand that you get about 2-3 ac out of the serp bracers - I would suggest going with Symbols of Loyalty to Vox.  For necklace, again go with something that gives you AC - if you're lucky, you'll get no effect from the DEX of the choker, and maybe 1-2 ac from the AGI.  For the waist, again, find something that gives you ac.</P><P>Basically, stats do almost nothing in this game for melees, other than a very, very minor effect for STR, and the above-listed importance of STA.  AC, on the other hand, is king at low levels (resists at high) - all the stories you hear about level 50 monks blowing away the AC of level 50 warriors are true, but they only happen when the monk has made a conscious effort to maximize AC rather than stats.</P><P>Weapon choice looks fine, although I'd recommend you get a fighting baton when you get the chance.  For HTH, a Ulak is likely the best HTH weapon you'll find for a long, long time.</P><P><i>Edit:  Also, be aware that the bracers you've listed, as well as the ones I listed, cannot be worn by Iksar monks, as Iksar cannot wear plate.</i></P><P>--------------------<BR>Hizuka - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=481" target=_blank>Profile</a><BR>Swifttail Disciple<BR>Initiate of the Celestial Fists<BR>Innoruuk Server<BR><BR>"I do not feel obliged to believe that the same God who has endowed us with sense, reason, and intellect has intended us to forgo their use."<BR><i>- Galileo Galilei </i></P><P>Message edited by: Hizuka (1/9/2002 6:20:18 AM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
